The paper also touches upon the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on image data and pixel-wise classification makes it likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The use of neural networks for image segmentation also suggests that the paper could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's discussion of data augmentation techniques, such as flipping and rotating images, suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category, which often deals with natural language data augmentation techniques.
